<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Drunkard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I find myself lately thinking about the fx on our armor. Before the nerf/balancing on the BPs, I really didn't care about how useless the other armor fx where because I felt the BPs made up for the difference.  Now that the BP where changed, I think verant owes up some better fx on the other pieces as compenstation. <BR>The kunark armor isn't too bad. The BP, legs, sleeves, and gloves have some use but helm, bracer, and boots are totally worthless.<BR>The velious armor is extremly bad. The legs are good but BP, bracer, and boots suck.  I personally wish they would add bulwark of faith or symbol of marzin on the velious BP because mark of karn still isn't worth the time to cast and resist rates on it are still very poor.<BR>I plan of starting a post on EQ boards about this but wanted to get some feedback first. Please post comments. Including maybe some fx  you'd like to see on the armor and please be  realistic on suggestions. I've been think along the lines of extinguish fatigue, counteract poison, atone(nice after heal agro changes), etc.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Asklepios Deiwos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Atone would be great.  Maybe put it on a helm, since it is a mind altering spell.<P>For the bracers I'd like to see a targetable Yaulp 3.<P>I wouldn't mind seeing Invis on one of the pieces.  If warriors can get it, I don't see why we can't.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What would be really cool, but we'll never see, would be armor that had an effect equal to the level of the player wearing it. <P>I.E. Donal's Gauntlets of Mourning have Aromor of Faith (level 39 spell). It would be nice if 49+ clerics using this actually casted Shield of Words, and 57+ clerics got Bulwark of Faith.<P>This would allow the cleric to cast a GOOD AC buff, and save ALOT of mana.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
